                  "key": "gen_ai.tool.call.arguments",
                  "value": {
                    "stringValue": "{\"command\":\"# Also check gpt-5.2 vs gpt-5.2-codex collision:\\necho \\\"gpt-5.2 length: $(echo -n 'gpt-5.2' | wc -c | tr -d ' ')\\\"\\necho \\\"gpt-5.2-codex length: $(echo -n 'gpt-5.2-codex' | wc -c | tr -d ' ')\\\"\\n# gpt-5.2: $1.75/$14 vs gpt-5.2-codex: $1.75/$14 -- same pricing! No observable collision issue.\\n\\n# Does gpt-5.3-codex match \\\"gpt-5.3\\\"? \\\"gpt-5.3\\\" is NOT in pricing table.\\n# But \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\" contains \\\"gpt-5\\\" (5 chars) and \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\" (13 chars)\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"gpt-5.3-codex length: $(echo -n 'gpt-5.3-codex' | wc -c | tr -d ' ')\\\"\\n# So if someone passes \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\", it gets \\\"gpt-5.3-codex\\\" (13 chars) over \\\"gpt-5\\\" (5 chars) -- correct\\n# But is there a gpt-5.3 entry? No. What about \\\"gpt-5.3\\\" as input? It would match \\\"gpt-5\\\" only. No test for this.\\n\\n# KEY FINDING: gpt-5.4, gpt-5.4-mini, gpt-5.4-nano all have different pricing\\n# and the longest-match behavior for this 3-way overlap is NOT tested\\n# (unlike gpt-5/gpt-5-mini and gpt-5.1-codex/gpt-5.1-codex-mini/max which are tested)\"}"
                  }
